This paper deals with self-stabilizing protocols in population models, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of time and space complexity, which falls under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Scientific Computing (cs.SC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of leader election, which is a common topic in the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
